data.title: List of Dark Castle Entertainment Films
data.text:
An amusement park mogul offers a group of diverse people $1,000,000 to spend the night in a haunted house with a horrifying past.

When Cyrus Kriticos, a very rich collector of unique things, dies, he leaves his house, fortune, and his prized collection of ghosts.

A salvage crew discovers a long-lost 1962 passenger ship floating lifeless in a remote region of the Bering Sea, and soon notices that its long-dead inhabitants may still be on board.

A psychiatrist awakens as a patient in a mental institution, with no memory of the murder she's accused of committing. As she tries to regain her memory, a vengeful spirit manipulates her.

A group of teens are unwittingly stranded near a strange wax museum and soon must fight to survive and keep from becoming the next exhibit.

A former Christian missionary, who specializes in debunking religious phenomena, investigates a small town which seems to be suffering from the 10 biblical plagues.

When a Russian mobster orchestrates a crooked land deal, millions of dollars are up for grabs, drawing in the entire London underworld into a feeding frenzy at a time when the old criminal regime is losing turf to a wealthy foreign mob.

A group of young horror fans go searching for a film that mysteriously vanished years ago but instead find that the demented killer from the movie is real, and he's thrilled to meet fans who will die gruesomely for his art.

A husband and wife who recently lost their baby adopt a 9-year-old girl who is not nearly as innocent as she appears.

U.S. Marshal Carrie Stetko tracks a killer in Antarctica as the sun is about to set for six months.

A young ninja turns his back on the orphanage that raised him, leading to a confrontation with a fellow ninja from the clan.

Genetic engineers Clive Nicoli and Elsa Kast hope to achieve fame by successfully splicing together the DNA of different animals to create new hybrid animals for medical use.

A CIA special forces team is betrayed and left for dead by their superiors, galvanizing them to mount an offensive on the CIA.

When a man awakens from a coma only to discover that someone has taken on his identity, he teams up with a young woman to prove who he is.

A couple is haunted by a supernatural presence that is unleashed during a college experiment.

An obsessed cop is on the trail of a serial killer prowling the streets of Buffalo, N.Y. but when his teenage daughter disappears, he drops any professional restraint to get the killer.

After watching their respective partners die, a New Orleans hitman and a Washington, D.C. detective form an alliance in order to bring down their common enemy.

To save his kidnapped wife, Brent Magna must drive at the orders of a mysterious man.

As a 1950s suburban community self-destructs, a home invasion has sinister consequences for one seemingly normal family.

Camille, a young woman who arrives at the Fairfield Academy following one of the student's untimely and violent death.
